div1.p: Teritory of Washington County of Jefferson } ss
To the sheriff of Jeffferson County
In persuance of an order this day made by the Hon B. F. Dennison Judge of the third judical District of Washington Territory

You are commanded in the name of the United States of America, to have the body of A.N. Jones, before the said Hon. B. F. Dennison Judge of the third judicial District of Washington Territory at the Court House in Port Townsend, Jefferson County, W. T. at nine O'Clock A.M. May 8th A.D. 1869 then and there to do and recive what shall be ordered concerning him and have you then and there this writ.
Witness the Hon BF Dennison Associate Justice Washinton Teritory and Judge of the third Judical district this 7th day May, AD 1869

Served the within by having the within named A N Jones before this court. he being held by a writ of Execution againt body issued out of the Justice court by W. L. Chalmers Justice of the peace for Jefferson county a copy of wich is here and to anexed and by me the authority
D. M. Littlefield Sheriff of Jefferson County W.T.
Subscribed and Sworn to before me this 8th day of May 1869 J.P. Nelson
